1.1: Basic HTML page with Bootstrap 5 via CDN

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Bootstrap 5 CDN Example</title>

  <!-- Bootstrap 5 CSS CDN -->
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.4.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />

</head>
<body>

  <div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="text-primary">Hello, Bootstrap 5!</h1>
    <button class="btn btn-success">Click Me</button>
  </div>

  <!-- Bootstrap 5 JS Bundle with Popper -->
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.4.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

</body>
</html>

1.2: Set up project with npm and use downloaded Bootstrap files
Step 1: Initialize project and install Bootstrap
mkdir my-bootstrap-project
cd my-bootstrap-project

npm init -y
npm install bootstrap@5

Step 2: Create HTML file (e.g., index.html) and link local Bootstrap files
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Bootstrap 5 Local Files Example</title>

  <!-- Link Bootstrap CSS from node_modules -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" />
</head>
<body>

  <div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="text-danger">Bootstrap 5 with npm</h1>
    <button class="btn btn-primary">Click Me</button>
  </div>

  <!-- Bootstrap JS Bundle -->
  <script src="node_modules/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

</body>
</html>
Step 3: Serve project with a simple server (optional)
Open this index.html in a browser directly or use a dev server:
npx live-server
or
npx http-server
